<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
A dark species (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 5, 6" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 5, 6. Senaspis species, habitus, lateral view 5 S. haemorrhoa (Gerstaecker) (♂) 6 S. melanthysana (Speiser) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures5-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486699" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">6</figureCitation>
) without distinct macula on wing but with darker medial area (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 74–76" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figures 74 - 76. Senaspis species, right wing 74 S. melanthysana (Speiser) (♂) 75 S. nigrita (Bigot) (♂) 76 S. nr umbrifera (Walker) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures74-76" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486718" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">74</figureCitation>
). It can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. nigrita" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the basal half of the scutellum largely concolourous with the scutum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 56–59" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figures 56 - 59. Senaspis species, thorax, dorsal view 56 S. flaviceps Macquart (♂) 57 S. haemorrhoa (Gerstaecker) (♂) 58 S. melanthysana (Speiser) (♂) 59 S. nigrita (Bigot) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures56-59" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486714" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">58</figureCitation>
) (scutellum largely yellow, contrasting with dark scutum in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. nigrita" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 56–59" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figures 56 - 59. Senaspis species, thorax, dorsal view 56 S. flaviceps Macquart (♂) 57 S. haemorrhoa (Gerstaecker) (♂) 58 S. melanthysana (Speiser) (♂) 59 S. nigrita (Bigot) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures56-59" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486714" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">59</figureCitation>
). It resembles strongly 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. umbrifera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="umbrifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. umbrifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be differentiated by the following characters: metafemur moderately thickened and straight to slight convex ventrally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 86–90" captionStartId="F25" captionText="Figures 86 - 90. Senaspis species, hind leg, anterior view 86 S. melanthysana (Speiser) (♂) 87 S. nigrita (Bigot) (♂) 88 S. nr umbrifera (Walker) (♂) 89 S. xanthorrhoea (Bezzi) (♂) 90 S. pennata (Herve-Bazin) (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures86-90" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486721" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">86</figureCitation>
) (thicker and concave in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. umbrifera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="umbrifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. umbrifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 86–90" captionStartId="F25" captionText="Figures 86 - 90. Senaspis species, hind leg, anterior view 86 S. melanthysana (Speiser) (♂) 87 S. nigrita (Bigot) (♂) 88 S. nr umbrifera (Walker) (♂) 89 S. xanthorrhoea (Bezzi) (♂) 90 S. pennata (Herve-Bazin) (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures86-90" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486721" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">88</figureCitation>
); abdomen with long dark pile along lateral margins (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 91–96" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figures 91 - 96. Senaspis species, abdomen, dorsal view 91 S. dentipes (Macquart) (♂) 92 S. dibapha (Walker) (♂) 93 S. elliotii Austen (♂) 94 S. flaviceps Macquart (♂) 95 S. haemorrhoa (Gerstaecker) (♂) 96 S. melanthysana (Speiser) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures91-96" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486722" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">96</figureCitation>
) (mixed short pale and dark pile in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. umbrifera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="umbrifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. umbrifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 97–101" captionStartId="F27" captionText="Figures 97 - 101. Senaspis species, abdomen, dorsal view 97 S. nigrita (Bigot) (♂) 98 S. umbrifera (Walker) (♂ holotype) 99 S. nr umbrifera (Walker) (♂) 100 S. xanthorrhoea (Bezzi) (♀) 101 S. pennata (Herve-Bazin) (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures97-99" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486723" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">98</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 97–101" captionStartId="F27" captionText="Figures 97 - 101. Senaspis species, abdomen, dorsal view 97 S. nigrita (Bigot) (♂) 98 S. umbrifera (Walker) (♂ holotype) 99 S. nr umbrifera (Walker) (♂) 100 S. xanthorrhoea (Bezzi) (♀) 101 S. pennata (Herve-Bazin) (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures97-99" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486723" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">99</figureCitation>
); long dark pile on all sterna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 5, 6" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 5, 6. Senaspis species, habitus, lateral view 5 S. haemorrhoa (Gerstaecker) (♂) 6 S. melanthysana (Speiser) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures5-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486699" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">6</figureCitation>
) (pale pile on sterna II and III in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. umbrifera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="umbrifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. umbrifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 9, 10" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 9, 10. Senaspis species, habitus, lateral view 9 S. umbrifera (Walker) (♂ holotype) 10 S. nr umbrifera (Walker) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures9-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486701" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
